server creation = nodejs+ express
-----------------------------
basic commands
--------------------
1)creation of the package.json - npm init
2)creation of the node modules- npm i express(installing of express)




basic steps
 
-------------------

1)creation a folder (bankserver)
2)create package.json
3)install express
4)create index.js
5)import express inside the index.js
6)create an app using the express
7)set up port number
8)resolve http request
    get -- to get the data
    post--to post the data
    put--upadate the data partially
    patch-update the data completely
    delete-dele the data completely 

9)HTTP Response Code
    1xx - Information
    2xx - successful
    3xx - redirection
    4xx - Client Error
    5xx - Server Error




     

    API request
    registration request
    login request
    deposit request
    withdraw request
    transaction request
    delete request



    jwt token -authentication
    to check login or not
    login...........token generate---->client-----------req to deposite+token------>server token check?

10) install JWT-  npm i jsonwebtoken
   To generate a token- sign()

   11)middileware--to verify the token
     it comes in the middle of the request and reponse cycle of the nodejs execution process
      

      1)application specifaction middleware
         ---for the entire application

          req,res,next

      2)router specific middileware
        ---- validation form


        12)database integration
          1)install mongoose  - npm i mongoose


        13)Asynchronous function resolving - promise
           1)Resolve State - .then()
           2)Reject state - .catch()


        1)Cors - Cross origin resource sharing
           
           install cors - nom i cors

           port 4200 (angular)--------request---->3000(node)(receive)

        14)Asynchronous call -RxJs-(Reactive Extension for JavaScript)
           
           JS-promise
           TS-RxJs(library)

             1)observable
               a)resolved -subscribe()
               b)reject-  catch